JUCE is an open-source cross-platform C++ application framework, used for the 
development of desktop and mobile applications. JUCE is used in particular for 
its GUI and plug-ins libraries. It is dual licensed under the AGPLv3 and a 
commercial license.

The aim of JUCE is to allow software to be written such that the same source 
code will compile and run identically on Windows, macOS and Linux platforms. 
It supports various development environments and compilers.

This requires: ladspa_sdk jack webkit2gtk4.1 cmake-opt gendesk 
